AIA, Huadian Power, Zijin Mining: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-04-14T11:08:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/aia-huadian-power-zijin-mining-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  fell 0.5 percent to 24,014. The Hang
Seng  China  Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, dropped 0.6 percent to 13,481.73.  AIA Group Ltd. (1299)  (1299 HK): The third-largest Asia-based
insurer by market value said it appointed Garth Jones group
chief financial officer, replacing Marc de Cure who resigned
after six months in the job. The stock gained 1.4 percent to
HK$24.75.  Huadian Power International Corp. (1071 HK): The power
producer said its power generation for the first quarter rose
about 28 percent from the same period a year earlier. The stock
gained 1.2 percent to HK$1.70.  Zijin Mining Group Co. (2899 HK): China’s biggest gold
producer by market value may purchase more shares in Glencore
International AG’s initial public offering after the allocation
phase “if the price is attractive,” Vice Chairman Lan Fusheng
said. Zijin Mining increased 0.2 percent to HK$6.28.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in  Tokyo  at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 